- Run npm init -y to create a package.json file
- Turn .js files into binary executables by adding a bin object in package.json
- Run npx link to link nls globally (delete all files in C:\Users\yourName\AppData\Roaming\npm if there's an error)
- Run npx install chalk to format console.log output
- Use Promise.all to allow parallel threads and to allow synchronous execution
- Dependency in package.json is the dependencies of the project
- Usage: Run "nls <dir>" in the command line. It works just like ls. Blue means directory, white means file.